$interpreted: Kittyeyes: It's been a while and he still hasn't come back... You think he took the money and ran?
Diana: No, I don't think he would do such a thing.
Team Captain: Sorry I took so long!
Kittyeyes: This is your team? That's it?
Team Captain: Ah, well... Yes, unfortunately our best players were all bought out.
Diana: That's quite alright, it's about quality, not quantity! We just have to try our best!
Team Captain: Well said! And I'll have you know my team is rip-roaring and ready to go!
Diana: How about registration and equipment?
Team Captain: I've got it all taken care of, thanks to your generous investment.
Team Captain: Alright, listen up everyone. This is the competition schedule.
Jerome: We've got the opening dance, water wars, dodgeball, and the crab run. Four in total!
Team Captain: Pay attention, the scores are tallied differently for each, and each team member can only compete once!
Diana: So we'll have to make sure we pick the best-suited team member for each event.
Team Captain: Hmm... The trickiest might be the opening dance. Teams usually have women do that event, but our team...
Diana: It's alright, I can do it.
Kittyeyes: Eh? You can dance, Diana?
Diana: I can learn.
Team Captain: I only ask because this event only requires one participant per team.
Diana: Oh really? Well then... do you have any tips for me?
Team Captain: Tips? Ah, not really, they just judge your dance...
Team Captain: But I guess they do tend to like the whole sweet, 'cute' persona. Full of energy, that whole thing.
Kittyeyes: Ah, well... If you want cute, then there's always Nolva...
Nolva: ......
Kittyeyes: Nolva, are you sleeping again!? Come on...
Jerome: If Nolva could fall asleep at any time, she might not be the best for a dance competition.
Kittyeyes: Agh... Fine, I'll do it!!

Diana: Thank you, Kittyeyes. I appreciate it... 
 Well, then, who should we pick for the next event?
Jerome: So the next one is some kind of battle royale... I'll join this one. Who else wants to join?
Team Captain: Hold on, this is probably a key event for getting points. We should be careful who we pick for this one.
Jerome: Huh? But it doesn't say there's a limit.
Team Captain: Yeah, but they take off points whenever someone is eliminated, so having a big team isn't the best idea. We should choose our best guy.
Diana: Well then I think it would be best to let Jerome do it. He's an experienced soldier. I trust he'll do a good job.
Team Captain: ...Alright, then. I'll take your word for it, since he's your friend and all.
Diana: (Friend...)
Team Captain: Then I guess it's no wonder you're dressed like that! You're all ready to battle, hah!
Jerome: Ah, no, this is just...
Kittyeyes: Hey~ Jerome, you've been expecting this the whole time, huh? I guess a good soldier's always prepared!
Jerome: Kittyeyes...
Diana: Hehe...
Team Captain: Great! Then the crab run obviously goes to me and Crabbie here! We're the best!
Diana: Eh?
Athlete: Don't look at Cap like that, Diana! He's really a crab-run master! He's won it more times than I can count!

Diana: Alright, well he certainly seems confident about it. 
 Finally, we've got dodgeball.
Team Captain: Oh, dodgeball's another elimination-type event. The last man standing only gets 10 points, though, so it's not a gamebreaker.
Team Captain: Our team has always been pretty great at dodgeball, though! Check it out!
Team Captain: Pretty impressive, huh?
Kittyeyes: Nolva...
Team Captain: Wow, she's... she's incredible!
Team Captain: Crabbie!?
Team Captain: I never thought there'd be someone else who could ride Crabbie...
Diana: Just luck, that's all!
Jerome: Are you okay?
Kittyeyes: Diana!?
Diana: I'm fine.
Jerome: You're hurt...
Diana: I'm fine, really.
Jerome: ......
Team Captain: I'm sorry Crabbie hurt you...
Diana: Now, back to business... I think I should participate in dodgeball, too. Then everyone will have an event.
Team Captain: No way! Even if you are our sponsor, as long as I'm the captain I won't let an injured team member play!
Diana: If I don't join, then we won't have enough people.
Team Captain: Don't worry, I think our final team member just woke up.
Nolva: Hmm...? Why's everyone looking at me?
Team Captain: Good morning!
Team Captain: We're going to need you to join in on the dodgeball event! If you do, I just know we'll win for sure!
Nolva: Eh!? What are you talking about!?
Kittyeyes: He's serious, Nolva. You just...
Nolva: No, that... that wasn't me! I can't do it!
Team Captain: Don't be modest, you were incredible just now! I've never seen anything like it!
Nolva: But...
Kittyeyes: No buts! It was amazing!
Nolva: ...Alright, I'll try...
Diana: Great, then everything is settled.
Team Captain: Then would you like to lead us in the team chant, Diana?
Diana: Ah, maybe you'd be better suited for that, since you're the team captain.
Team Captain: No, I insist. If it weren't for you, we wouldn't be here right now, with this great opportunity.
Diana: Okay everybody, we all have a difficult task ahead of us! But what would we be without difficulties? Without obstacles?
Diana: I believe... No, I know that all of us have what it takes to win it! As long as we help each other, we can do anything we set our minds to!
Diana: Can you feel it to!? Do you believe in yourselves, and in all of us!?
Kittyeyes: I believe it!!
Nolva: Let's be the best there is!
Jerome: Let's do it!
Diana: That's what I want to hear! Let's bring home the gold!
Diana: (It's almost time for the competition... should I really be doing this?)
Diana: Is that... Kittyeyes?
Kittyeyes: D-D-Diana!? You're still awake?
Diana: Mm... I can't sleep. Are you still practicing?
Kittyeyes: Yeah... I still feel like I've got a ways to go...
Diana: I'm sorry, having you do something you're not good at.
Kittyeyes: Don't say it like that! I wanted to help. Plus, I'm not the only one training hard.
Diana: But I do feel bad getting you all wrapped up in this.
Kittyeyes: I, uh... In the past I was sort of held captive, in servitude.
Diana: Huh?
Kittyeyes: If it weren't for Roger, I might have never escaped that life.
Kittyeyes: So I can understand how hard these athletes have it. I can understand hard work.
Diana: So you want to help them as much as you can, even if it means staying up all night to train...
Kittyeyes: Can you understand that, Diana?
Kittyeyes: You said you're doing this because you don't like the way those thugs were treating the teams, but... Is there another reason?
Kittyeyes: I mean... for someone like Jerome to be so respectful in front of you...
Kittyeyes: And the way you just invested all that money, and the way you talk... I figure you're a really important person, right?
Diana: ......
Kittyeyes: Heh, I guess I've got a better sense for people than I thought. Maybe because I met all sorts in my old life...
Diana: That's because...
Kittyeyes: You don't have to explain. I know you're not a bad person.
Diana: Sometimes, people need to help each other. To push each other.
Diana: And it just so happens I know another group of people who've come across disaster, and are doing their best to rebuild.
Diana: ...And I just can't sit by and watch it happen, without lending a hand.
Kittyeyes: You must put yourself through a lot.
Diana: ...I'm used to it. It's the right thing to do.
Kittyeyes: But Diana, aren't you forgetting something?
Diana: Forgetting something?
Kittyeyes: I said I wanted to help because we're friends. And you responded.
Diana: ...Miss Kittyeyes.
Kittyeyes: If we're friends, then you can drop the 'Miss'. Just Kittyeyes, alright? It's not fair if I'm just calling you 'Diana'.
Diana: Okay, Kittyeyes.
Nolva: Uh...
Nolva: Jerome, did you already know how Diana felt?
Jerome: There are some things that don't need talking about.
Jerome: But I didn't lie to you.
Nolva: I know... I know I can trust you.
Jerome: Enough with the compliments. Let's just do our best, alright?
